In [[Korun/Legends|Korunnai]] society, a '''Ghôsh''' was essentially a tribe or family. One such example was [[Ghôsh Windu]], the tribe to which [[Mace Windu/Legends|Mace Windu]] belonged. Another was [[Ghôsh Rostu]]. Members of the same ghôsh were referred to as [[Dôshalo]]. If a child's parents were killed before their naming day, the child would become a ''[[nidôsh]]'', or clan child, and take the clan's name as his own.

